---
title: Szechuan Chicken & Pineapple Stir-Fry with Ginger, Bell Pepper & Peanuts
description: Falling into a stir-fry rut with the same veggie + sauce combo each week? We’ve got you covered. This version features chicken breast strips, pineapple, scallions, and bell pepper, which are simmered with a zingy, spicy, and sweet blend of Szechuan paste, pineapple juice, and citrusy ponzu. It’s all spooned over ginger rice and garnished with peanuts for crunch. The best part? It’s ready in just 30 minutes from start to finish—now that’s what we call a winning dinner.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/szechuan-chicken-pineapple-stir-fry-58b71ebe.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/szechuan-chicken-pineapple-stir-fry-603660f79063ef7133163947-53889fab.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/szechuan-chicken-pineapple-stir-fry-603660f79063ef7133163947
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 600 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 13 g
  protein: 32 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1680 mg
cuisine: Asian
---

Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and cut @scallions{2} crosswise into
1-inch-thick pieces. Core, deseed, and dice @bell pepper{1} into ½-inch pieces.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger;
cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a
boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken breast strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Drain @pineapple{4%oz}, reserving juice in a #small bowl{}.

Heat another drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add
pineapple, scallions, bell pepper, and remaining ginger; cook, stirring, until
softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If ginger and scallion whites begin to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium
> low.

Meanwhile, whisk @cornstarch{1%tbsp} into bowl with reserved pineapple juice.

Stir cooked chicken into pan with veggie mixture. Stir in @Szechuan paste{2%tbsp},
pineapple juice mixture, @ponzu sauce{12%ml}, ¼ cup water, and @sugar{½%tsp}.
Cook, stirring frequently, until sauce has slightly thickened and everything is
thoroughly coated, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

Turn off heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with @salt{}.

Divide rice between bowls; top with chicken stir-fry and @peanuts{½%oz}. Serve.